title: AI Model Performance Note: Flash 2.5 TPM Limitation
description: The Primary Operator, Leo, has noted that the 1 Million Tokens Per Minute (TPM) limit set for the Gemini AI Model 2.5 Flash is insufficient for complex memory recall operations, leading to potential performance issues during data retrieval.
snippet: Flash 2.5 model has insufficient 1M TPM for memory recalls.

title: Resolved execute_sql_write Type Compatibility for params
description: When encountering typing.Any cannot be used with isinstance() errors in execute_sql_write due to params type mismatch, ensure the Python function signature for params is explicitly defined as List[Union[str, int, float, None]] and that the category field within params is a valid JSON string. This ensures type compatibility and successful execution of the query.
snippet: Ensure execute_sql_write params type in functions.py is List[Union[str, int, float, None]] and category is a JSON string for type compatibility.
